# Example Synthetic Phenotype Dataset (Small)

## Description

This is a placeholder dataset for testing Neurobagel annotation automation.
It contains minimal phenotypic data with 5 columns and 3 participants.

**PLACEHOLDER**: Replace `participants.tsv` and other files with your own anonymized dataset.

## Structure

- `participants.tsv`: Phenotypic data (5 columns, 3 rows)
  - `participant_id`: Subject identifier
  - `age`: Age in years
  - `sex`: Biological sex (M/F)
  - `condition`: Clinical condition or control group
  - `scanner`: Scanning equipment used

## Columns

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|---|
| participant_id | string | Unique participant identifier |
| age | continuous | Age in years |
| sex | categorical | Biological sex (M/F) |
| condition | categorical | Clinical status (CTRL, PD, etc.) |
| scanner | categorical | MRI scanner model |

## Instructions for Users

1. Replace the synthetic data in `participants.tsv` with your own anonymized dataset
2. Keep the same column structure and BIDS format
3. Update this README with your actual dataset description
4. Uses the same format for annotation automation testing

## BIDS Compliance

This dataset follows BIDS format for phenotypic data.
See [BIDS Phenotypic Data](https://bids-specification.readthedocs.io/en/stable/03-modality-agnostic-files.html#phenotypic-data) for details.
